        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "children": [
            {
              "bold": true,
              "text": "How does it work?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The short version is that the blog is entirely generated during build-time using Next.js static site generation and the content for the blog is made available during build-time using Keystone's powerful content platform along with the magic of zero configuration file-system based SQLite database."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unordered-list",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "list-item",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "list-item-content",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "The blog is generated statically using "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "href": "https://nextjs.org/docs/advanced-features/static-html-export",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "Next.js static HTML export"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "list-item",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "list-item-content",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "The content for the blog is fetched from a "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "href": "https://keystonejs.com/",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "local Keystone server"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ". Keystone is a fantastic content platform that auto-magically generates GraphQL API based on schema definitions."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "list-item",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "list-item-content",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Usually content platforms need to be connected to a database and hosted somewhere which often comes with hosting, configuration and maintenance cost. "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "href": "https://keystonejs.com/docs/apis/config#sqlite",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "Keystone supports SQLite database"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " and we make use of that to avoid having to configure, host or maintain anything. "
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "You can get started with zero configuration and commit your database along with your code like any other file.",
                      "bold": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " 🤯 This is what makes this whole "
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "generate blogs locally without having to host a server anywhere",
                      "italic": true
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " possible."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "list-item",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "list-item-content",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "Author your content visually in your local environment using "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "href": "https://keystonejs.com/docs/guides/document-field-demo",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "Keystone's powerful document editor"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " and admin dashboard. Once your content is ready, just run a local build and your blog will be exported as a static website. Now you can easily host this static website anywhere. I created "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "href": "https://dineshpandiyan.com/",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "my blog"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " using this template and hosted it in "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "link",
                      "href": "https://www.netlify.com/",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "Netlify"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ". Every time I make a change to my content, all I gotta do is push my changes to the repo and Netlify automatically deploys it in less than a minute."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "list-item",
