        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "How is this different from MDX based blogs?",
              "bold": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The idea is same - you statically generate your blog using content made available during build-time. The difference however, is that, MDX authored content is passed through a plugin system during the build and the content is made available in your pages to be built. This is easy as long as you only need the default out-of-the-box markdown syntax content. The moment you want to customise your content with fancier components (Eg. carousel, YouTube video, Twitter embed, syntax highlighted code, Hero image, etc) you will either have to find a plugin that supports that or build them yourself which sometimes can get quite cumbersome."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "This is where "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "href": "https://keystonejs.com/docs/guides/document-field-demo#document-fields-demo",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Keystone's all powerful document field"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " comes into play. You can author content using a visual editor and see how your content is going to look while authoring it. And most importantly Keystone's document field makes it easy to add custom components (Eg. "
            },
            {
              "text": "carousel, YouTube video, Twitter embed, syntax highlighted code, Hero image, etc",
              "italic": true
            },
            {
              "text": "). All you need to know to add a custom component is to know how to code in React and voila. 🥳 This template is setup with a few custom components ("
            },
            {
              "text": "hero image, custom blockquote, embed tweet, embed youtube videos, callouts and syntax highlighted code blocks",
              "italic": true
            },
            {
              "text": "). You can see the custom components in action here — "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "href": "https://staticblogswithkeystone.netlify.app/blog/keystone-content-authoring",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Keystone Content Authoring Experience is Just Fantastic!"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Keystone's document editor stands out in a handful of ways over MDX based content —"
